            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/9/Affinity-2.png" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <p>It has always been a dream of mine to be able to create any logo or complete brand identity I want in a vector program. I've been dabbling and playing around on an off with different apps like Illustrator, Inkscape and now, Affinity. I have a lot of ideas in my head for designs and I just want to build those best I can. In order for me to brush up my vector skills, I'm now taking "<a href="https://www.udemy.com/course/how-to-make-logos-in-affinity-designer" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">How to Make Logos in Affinity Designer</a>", by Affinity Revolution. </p>
<figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/9//Affinity.png" alt="" width="1610" height="327" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcset="https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/9//responsive/Affinity-xs.png 300w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/9//responsive/Affinity-sm.png 480w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/9//responsive/Affinity-md.png 768w ,https://www.fassbender.studio/media/posts/9//responsive/Affinity-lg.png 1024w"></figure>
<p>Even though the course may look "simple" and is aimed at beginners, that's exactly what I need now! I will be logging my progress in the course here. Stay tuned!  </p>
